ge

greater than or equal, >= operator.

Syntax

C = ge(A, B)
C = (A >= B)

Input argument

A

a variable

B

a variable

Output argument

C

result of A >= B

Description

C = ge(A, B) returns a logical array with elements set to logical true A is greater than or equal to B.

Examples

eye(2,2) >= ones(2, 2)


0 >= i


'Nelson' >= 'Noslen'


'Nelson' >= 'l'


ge(0.8-0.6-0.2, 0)

See also

ne, lt, le, gt, eq.
